    <abstract id="ab005">
      <p><bold>KaKs_Calculator</bold> 3.0 is an updated toolkit that is capable of calculating <bold>selective pressure</bold> on both <bold>coding</bold> and <bold>non-coding</bold> sequences. Similar to the nonsynonymous/synonymous <bold>substitution</bold> rate ratio for coding sequences, selection on non-coding sequences can be quantified as the ratio of non-coding nucleotide substitution rate to synonymous substitution rate of adjacent coding sequences. As testified on empirical data, KaKs_Calculator 3.0 shows effectiveness to detect the strength and mode of selection operated on molecular sequences, accordingly demonstrating its great potential to achieve genome-wide scan of natural selection on diverse sequences and identification of potentially functional elements at a whole-genome scale. The package of KaKs_Calculator 3.0 is freely available for academic use only at <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://ngdc.cncb.ac.cn/biocode/tools/BT000001" id="ir005">https://ngdc.cncb.ac.cn/biocode/tools/BT000001</ext-link>.</p>
